PRIVACY POLICY — DocVault
Last updated: 3 May 2026

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

1. INTRODUCTION
DocVault ("we", "our", or "the app") is a private document management application.
This Privacy Policy explains how DocVault handles information when you use the app.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

2. INFORMATION WE COLLECT

2.1 Data stored locally on your device
DocVault stores the following data exclusively on your device:
  • Scanned document images and generated PDF files
  • Document metadata (name, category, date, file size)
  • Your chosen authentication method (biometric or passcode)
  • A hashed record of whether you have accepted this policy

DocVault does NOT transmit any of your documents or personal data to any server
or third party. All storage is local to your device only.

2.2 Camera and Photo Library
With your permission, DocVault accesses:
  • The device camera — to scan and capture document pages
  • The photo library — to import existing images as document pages

These permissions are requested at runtime. You may revoke them at any time via
your device Settings.

2.3 Biometric data
If you enable biometric authentication (Face ID / fingerprint), DocVault relies
entirely on the device's native biometric API (provided by Apple or Google).
DocVault never stores, reads, or transmits raw biometric data.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

3. HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION
The data described in Section 2 is used solely to provide the features of the app:
  • Displaying and organising your documents
  • Generating PDFs from scanned pages
  • Protecting access to the app with biometrics or a passcode

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

4. DATA SHARING
We do not share, sell, rent, or transfer your data to any third party.
The only time document files leave your device is when you explicitly choose to
share a document using the device's native share sheet.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

5. DATA RETENTION AND DELETION
All data is stored locally on your device. You can delete individual documents
from within the app at any time. Uninstalling the app removes all app data from
your device in accordance with iOS / Android standard behaviour.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

6. SECURITY
  • Passcodes are stored in the device's secure keychain / keystore.
  • Biometric authentication uses the device's built-in secure enclave.
  • No network connections are made by the app.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

7. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
DocVault is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect any
personal information from children.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

8. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The latest version will
always be available at the URL shown in the app's splash screen. Continued use
of the app after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

9. CONTACT
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please open an issue on the
project's GitHub repository.

